===Etymology===
From {{etyl|fr}} ''[[#French|différance]]'' ‘deferral’ (coined in this sense by [[w:Jacques Derrida|Derrida]]), from ''[[différer]]'' ‘to postpone’; but punning on ''[[différence]]'' ‘difference’.

===Noun===
{{en-noun|-}}

# {{context|literary theory|linguistics}} The endless deferral of any ultimate meaning in a word or sentence, owing to the necessity of recourse to a potentially infinite series of other, equally uncertain words or signs.

